The paper deals with the complexity of temporal logic model checking and the size of data structures used in symbolic model checking. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with temporal logic model checking, which is a subfield of logic in computer science. 

cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of preprocessing to improve performance in model checking, which is a common technique used in programming languages. 

cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the size of data structures used in symbolic model checking. 

cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the industrial applications of model checking, which is a common technique used in software engineering. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of BDDs and other data structures, which are also used in machine learning.
